  "doc_id": "24312",
  "text": "This patient presented us with a treatment dichotomy involving both an ICT and significant hyperfibrinolysis. The first decision that needed to be made was how to treat the ICT. It has been suggested that clot lysis typically occurs within 30 minutes without exogenous fibrinolytic therapy as long as cardiac output can be maintained. [CITATION_1] This notion held true in our case as supportive care was immediately initiated in an attempt to maintain an adequate cardiac output and the clot resolved spontaneously. Given the rapid resolution of the thrombus and normalization of RV function with improved hemodynamics, no further treatment was warranted.",
